<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 5:59AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Craig, Rogers, Mayes
and Nowata Counties through 645 AM CDT...
At 559 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 3 miles east of South Coffeyville to 5 miles
northwest of New Alluwe to 2 miles south of Claremore. Movement was
east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Claremore...                      Vinita...
Nowata...                         Pryor...
Owasso...                         Pryor Creek...
Catoosa...                        Verdigris...
Chelsea...                        Salina...
Oologah...                        Langley...
Adair...                          South Coffeyville...
Welch...                          Ketchum...
Spavinaw...                       Delaware...
Foyil...                          Bluejacket...
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 240 and 292.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
